Korean Army and People Called upon to Glorify Songun Era 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Papers Sunday in editorials dedicated to the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission say that the past ten-odd years when he has led the Korean revolution, assuming a heavy responsibility of the NDC chairman, were the unforgettable years which have witnessed a significant turn in strengthening the state and the revolutionary armed forces and the glorious years when the heroic stamina of the DPRK dynamically advancing toward a bright future, overcoming manifold difficulties, was brought into full play.
 Over the past more than ten years Kim Jong Il has ushered in a new history of building a great prosperous powerful nation in this land by leading the party, the army and people with his unique Songun politics, Songun revolutionary leadership, Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK led by him is a country of single-minded unity where the headquarters of the revolution and the army and people have formed a harmonious whole.
 It is only in the DPRK that the leader, the army and the people have formed unbreakable ties of kinship based on warm love, trust and noble moral obligation.
 The DPRK led by him is an invincible military power which defends the dignity of the nation with powerful national defence capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The self-reliant national defence power of the DPRK has been remarkably strengthened. The whole army is replete with the spirit of devotedly defending the leader and all the servicepersons are reliably defending the country and socialism in the spirit of readily becoming human bombs, the spirit of suicide bombing. It has modern offensive and defensive means capable of coping with any war, the trait of attaching importance to arms prevails in the whole society and the all-people and nationwide defensive system has been firmly established. No force on earth can pounce upon the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that the DPRK has a bright future as it has Kim Jong Il, an illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu and a politician of general type, at the head of the army and the state.

Marathon Race for Mangyongdae Cup Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- The 19th International Marathon Race for Mangyongdae Cup was held here on Sunday in the run-up to the Day of the Sun.
 Its opening ceremony held at Kim Il Sung Stadium was attended by Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Tong Jong Ho, minister of Construction and Building-Materials Industries who is chairman of the DPRK Marathon Association, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Runners from South Africa, Norway, Romania, Botswana, China, Zimbabwe, Ethiopia, Kenya, Tanzania and the DPRK entered the stadium. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Jae Dok, chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, in an opening address said that the marathon race offers a significant occasion in boosting exchange and cooperation in sports field among different countries and jointly developing marathon technique. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The marathoners left the stadium and ran through the Arch of Triumph, Hyoksin Street, Yongung Street, Chollima Street, Rakwon Street and Kwangbok Street to the turn in Youth Hero Motorway and returned to the destination.
 A result of the race was published at the closing ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 DPRK marathoners Ri Kyong Chol and Jo Pun Hui who placed the first at the race were awarded trophy cups and gold medals, DPRK marathoners Ri Kum Song and Jong Yong Ok who placed the second silver medals and a Zimbabwean marathoner and DPRK marathoner Kim Kum Ok who placed the third bronze medals.

Performance Given to Open Moranbong Theater 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Moranbong Theater has been rebuilt on a modernization basis as an edifice of national value in the Songun era.
 The theatre on Moran Hill was opened on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.
 Its architectural form and content have been renovated on the best level and its stage, auditorium, training room, make-up room and other parts have been rebuilt to be peculiar and perfect in terms of plastic art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The theater was built on the initiative of President Kim Il Sung after the country's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Here he guided major party and state meetings, including the fourth and the fifth plenary meetings of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, 73 sessions of the Supreme People's Assembly and the Joint Conference of Representatives of Political Parties and Public Organizations in North and South Korea and watched art performances and conducted external activities on more than 200 occasions.
 At the first SPA session held here he was elected as head of state according to the unanimous desire of all the Koreans and the foundation of the DPRK was proclaimed here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An opening performance was given by the State Symphony Orchestra at the theatre today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance began with movement no. 4 "Glory to the General" of symphony suite "Long Road of Songun Leadership". The repertoire included orchestral music "Thunder on Jong Il Peak," "Arirang", "Pass Mungyong" and "Rich Harvest Comes to the Chongsan Plain", a collection of famous music such as orchestral music "Don't Advance, Night of Pyongyang." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance of high ideological and artistic value fully proved the validity of the WPK's policy on literature and art as it represented rich national aroma of the Juche-oriented combined orchestral music, various genre peculiar to orchestra and rich orchestral nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was appreciated by Kim Yong Nam, Pak Pong Ju, Jon Pyong Ho, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop and others and deputies to the SPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also among the audience were deputies to the SPA from  the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) including Ho Jong Man, chief vice-chairman of the Chongryon Central Standing Committee.

Kim Jong Il Inspects Sub-Unit of KPA Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 9 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, inspected the tank and armored car drivers training sub-unit of KPA Unit 604.
 He acquainted himself with the sub-unit's performance of duty. Then he mounted an observation platform to watch servicemen in training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They strikingly demonstrated that they have been fully prepared to successfully carry out any duty under any circumstances through their tireless actual maneuvers, bearing in mind his instruction that it is an important need of a modern warfare to increase the speed of the transport of a unit and its maneuverability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was satisfied to learn that the sub-unit has built a training ground suited to the contents of training and its features and waged a dynamic drive to carry through the policy of training laid down by the WPK, thus training many skilled tank and armored car drivers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round military lecture rooms, he acquainted himself in detail with how trainees are educated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very good for the sub-unit to have built well lecture rooms to give all the trainees sufficient serviceable knowledge needed for actual battles and effectively operated them for education and training, he said, stressing the need to thoroughly establish Juche in military education in order to fully prepare the servicepersons to be a-match-for-a hundred stalwart combatants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He took deep care of the service and living of the soldiers, making the rounds of an education room, a mess hall, a kitchen, a wash-cum-bath house, a non-staple food store, a barn and other places of the sub-unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was pleased to learn that the sub-unit has provided its servicepersons with good living conditions by building sufficient entertainment and educational and supply facilities. He praised such revolutionary fighting traits and lifestyle of the servicepersons as managing their economic life tenaciously and methodically just as the anti-Japanese guerrillas managed their unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the sub-unit. 
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong, Ri Yong Chol and Ri Jae Il, first vice department directors of the C.C., WPK, and Hwang Pyong So, vice department director of the same.

Day of Sun Commemorated Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- Meetings, seminar, lecture and reading session were held in Karachi and Lahore of Pakistan and Kinshasa of Democratic Congo and by the Congolese Socialist Party and Marien Ngouabi University of Congo from March 28 to 31 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. 
 Displayed in the venues of the functions were photos dealing with the glorious and brilliant revolutionary history of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il and their immortal exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Chairman of the National Workers' Party of Pakistan Abid Hussein and President of the Pakistan Socialist Party C. R. Aslam made speeches at the meetings. 
 They said that Kim Il Sung founded the Juche idea and Songun idea based on it, providing a powerful ideological and theoretical weapon for accomplishing the cause of independence against imperialism and making an immortal contribution to the Korean revolution and the accomplishment of the cause of global independence with his energetic leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the National Committee of the Genuine Lumumbist Patriotic Party of Democratic Congo Otete Gaston Mboyo noted that the immortal exploits performed by the President, a great thinker and distinguished statesman, would be always remembered by humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary of the Congolese Socialist Party Leon Nzokene in his lecture entitled "The eternal Party of Comrade Kim Il Sung" introduced in detail the history of the Workers' Party of Korea which has always emerged victorious under the leadership of the peerlessly great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Letters to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings held in Pakistan.

More Gifts Displayed at International Friendship Exhibition
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- More than 1,050 gifts presented to President Kim Il Sung, anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk and leader Kim Jong Il by revolutionary people of the world in 2005 have been added to the International Friendship Exhibition to be displayed in several rooms in a peculiar manner.
 Among them are a stationery box  presented to Kim Il Sung by Thaksin Shinawatra, leader of the Thai Rak Thai Party, a wooden handicraft "Carriage" presented to him by the foreign minister of Thailand, and a jewel handicraft "Tree of Hope" from Marcia de Campos Pereira, president of the Women's International Democratic Federation.
 On display at the general review room are silk banners presented to Kim Jong Suk by the chairman of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung National Memorial Commission, Nepal, and the representative of the Society of the Japan-Korea Culture and a glassware for fruits by the Swiss Committee for Supporting Korea's Independent and Peaceful Reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the newly arranged room are gifts Kim Jong Il received from heads of state of various countries. They include a ceramic vase presented by Russian President Putin, an oil painting "Scenery of Pinar del Rio Province" by Fidel Castro Ruz, first secretary of the C.C., the Communist Party of Cuba, president of the Council of State and president of the Council of Ministers of Cuba, a decorative porcelain dish by Abdullah II, king of the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan, and a wooden sculpture "African" by Zambian President Levy Patrick Mwanawasa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on display there are a glass craftwork "Daily Development" sent by Tang Jiaxuan, state councilor of China, a seal ivory product by K. Pulikovski, former special presidential envoy to the Far Eastern region of Russian, and a silver-plated wooden  tray by Megawati Soekarnoputri, former Indonesian president, six silver dishes and six silver spoons by Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, and gifts by Guy Dupre, secretary general of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, Jitendra Sharma, president of the International Association of Democratic Lawyers, and other personages of international and regional organizations.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Election as NDC Chairman Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- An evening gala of young vanguard of the Ministry of People's Security was held at the ministry and a meeting of agricultural workers on the educational ground of the Unryul Revolutionary Museum on April 7 to celebrate the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission.
 Present at the evening gala were Minister Ju Sang Song, Director of the Political Department Ji Yong Chun and other leading officials of the Ministry of People's Security and young servicepersons of the ministry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the venue of the evening gala began with "Song of General Kim Jong Il" such songs as "Our General Is Best", "Twelve Months of Songun Victory", "Let's Join in the Army of the General" and "Nilliri for Songun" were resounded one after another, adding delight to the dancing servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants danced full of vigor to the tune of such songs as "Let's Uphold Our General", "Pride of Youth" and "Arirang for Prosperity," waving flags of the supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, Party flags and flags of the DPRK.
 At the meeting of agricultural workers, Chairman of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea Kang Chang Uk made a congratulatory address, which was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers recalled that Kim Jong Il put forward the policies of bringing a radical turn in seed improvement and potato farming, double-cropping and soya bean cultivation and has energetically led the drive for their implementation.
 They noted that the land of the country was realigned as befitting the socialist land and the projects of Kaechon-Lake Thaesong and Paekma-Cholsan waterways were completed under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, thus making a breakthrough for more successful farming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called for working hard to make a new leap forward in the agricultural production and doing farm work well this year to decisively solve the food problem.
 Poem "Oath Taken before the Brilliant Commander of Songun" was recited at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the meeting an art performance was given.

Military Attaches' Corps Visits Revolutionary Site
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- The military attaches' corps here Friday visited the Phyongchon Revolutionary Site on the occasion of the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission.
 The visitors went round the relics and materials at the site, being briefed about the fact that President Kim Il Sung selected the site for the first ordnance manufactory to build the Juche-oriented national defence industry and personally had a test-fire with submachine guns manufactured by Korean workers themselves at the manufactory while indicating the orientation and ways for its development, and about the undying exploits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu for the development of the national defence industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They made an entry in the visitor's book. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Giraldo Abreu Morales, military attache of the Cuban Embassy who is doyen of the corps, wrote that Kim Il Sung attached great efforts to the building of national defence industry to turn the country into a powerful state to cope with the enemy's aggressive moves after its liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The members of the military attaches' corps warmly congratulate Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il, who is always winning victory after victory with his unique Songun revolutionary leadership by inheriting Kim Il Sung's cause of army building, on the 13th anniversary of his election as NDC chairman, he wrote.

National Art Exhibition Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- A national art exhibition was opened at the Korean Art Gallery on April 7 to commemorate the Day of the Sun, the greatest auspicious April holiday of the Korean nation.
 Displayed at the exhibition hall are Korean paintings, oil and acrylic paintings, posters and many other art works dealing with the undying feats President Kim Il Sung performed for the revolutionary cause of Juche and the leadership traits of          Kim Jong Il who has brilliantly carried forward the revolutionary cause of Kim Il Sung.
 Minister of Culture Kim Jin Song made an opening address and then the participants looked round the art works. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the works are oil painting "The Fatherly Leader Standing in Front of His Old Home in Mangyongdae", acrylic painting "The Great Sun of the World People", Korean painting "Kalun in Spring" and oil painting "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung Having Conversation with Peasants before the Agrarian Reform" which help the visitors emotionally recall the immortal personality of Kim Il Sung as a great man and his brilliant revolutionary life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are also such works as Korean painting "Leaving Footprints for Great Songun Leadership" and poster "Let's Uphold Supreme Commander Comrade Kim Jong Il with Loyalty!" dealing with the extraordinary exploits of Kim Il Sung who gave a steady continuity to the revolutionary leadership for Songun, and acrylic painting "Visiting the Snowy Tabaksol Post" and poster "The Songun Policy of Our Party Is a Treasured Sword for Sure Victory!" showing the greatness of Kim Jong Il.

Wonder in Sky over Secret Camp in Mt. Paektu
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- There took place a wonder in the sky over the secret camp in Mt. Paektu at a time when all the servicepersons and people of the DPRK are celebrating the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the National Defence Commission with splendor. 
 There appeared in the sky a double solar halo reminiscent of a rainbow at 7:00 a.m. on April 6, a rare phenomenon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day the temperature in the area covered with 75 cm of snow registered 11.2 deg. below zero or 1.5 deg. higher than that of last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Snow was seen flying dazzlingly in the area when the sun rose from the eastern sky clad in thin clouds in the early morning. It was against this background that a big and bright double solar halo, not yet in full round shape, appeared in the sky over the camp at the foot of Jong Il Peak. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This spectacular scenery lasted for 40 minutes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The officials of the meteorological station at the camp in Mt. Paektu said that it was a very rare natural phenomenon, the first of its kind in the history of meteorological observation in the area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials and other working people were very pleased to say that the double solar halo that appeared in the sky over the holy land of the Korean revolution in the run-up to the April auspicious jubilee reflects the warm congratulations the servicepersons and people are offering to Kim Jong Il.

Servicepersons of Ministry of People's Security Vow Their Loyalty
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- A meeting of servicepersons of the Ministry of People's Security was held in the plaza of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on April 7 to vow to uphold the Songun idea and leadership of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il with loyalty on the significant Day of the Sun.
 Present at the meeting were Minister of People's Security Ju Sang Song, Director of the Political Department of the ministry Ji Yong Chun, senior officials of the ministry, public security officials and persons in Pyongyang and local areas and servicepersons of the Korean People's Security Forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Led by the minister, all the participants made a solemn pledge to hold President Kim Il Sung in high esteem as the sun of Juche forever and remain true to the Songun leadership of  Kim Jong Il and thus exalt the honor of being political protectors of the Workers' Party of Korea in defending the country and building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They reiterated the will of all the members of the people's security institutions to become first-line protectors devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution and ardent Songun revolutionary comrades who take the lead in upholding Kim Jong Il's Songun idea and leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They pledged themselves to thoroughly establish state law and order and become staunch defenders of the Korean-style socialist system and true servants who devotedly work for the people and dedicate everything to protecting their interests, lives and properties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also vowed to continue making a long journey for the Songun revolution till its victory under the leadership of  Kim Jong Il no matter how the world may change and effect a revolutionary turn in the work to preserve people's security and thus bring earlier the day of the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche.
 The meeting closed with a chorus of the song "We Will Defend the Headquarters of Revolution with Our Lives". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then its participants marched past the tribune of honor in fine array.
 Meanwhile, a large chorus "Devotedly Defending the Leader Is Our Life" was presented by servicepersons of the Korean People's Security Forces at the ministry on the same day to commemorate the Day of the Sun.

Suppression of Anti-war Protestors in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- The Defence Ministry of south Korea has been getting overheated in crackdown upon the members of civic and public organizations who held a surprise demonstration to frustrate the joint landing exercises of the U.S. troops and south Korean army in the beach of Manripho in Thaean County, South Chungchong Province on March 30, according to south Korea's Yonhap news.
 On April 2 the ministry said that any illegal demonstration in the ground of joint landing exercises cannot be pardoned and the military would resolutely deal with such illegal action. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, on April 1 it reported to the police office more than 20 demonstrators including Ri Kyu Jae, chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification, on the charge of "hampering the execution of special official duty". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ferocious action of the south Korean military authorities is a frontal challenge to all the fellow countrymen aspiring after peace and reunification, and it clearly shows who really wants peace and who does not want reunification.

Nat�fl Meeting Marks 13th anniv. of Kim Jong Il's Election as NDC Chairman
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the April 25 House of Culture here on Saturday to celebrate the 13th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission.
 The meeting was attended by Kim Yong Nam, Jo Myong Rok, Pak Pong Ju, Kim Yong Chun, Jon Pyong Ho and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Il Chol, member of the DPRK NDC and minister of the People's Armed Forces, in a report said that Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the NDC marked an event of special mention as it was of epochal significance in guaranteeing a bright future of the country and the development of the Korean revolution in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The course of the revolution covered by the DPRK with him holding the chairmanship of the NDC represented years of a historic change as it has achieved a miraculous victory in its endeavors to defend socialism in the do-or-die spirit despite the unprecedentedly grim hardships and difficulties and paved a broad avenue for building a great prosperous powerful nation, he noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Shouldering upon himself the heavy responsibility as NDC chairman,
Kim Jong Il has fully provided the Songun revolutionary leadership to all aspects of state construction and activities, consolidating the Korean-style socialist state system and bringing about a great turn in the revolution and construction. The military position of the Korean revolution with the invincible KPA as the core has been consolidated as firm as an iron wall and the DPRK proudly emerged a world military power with nuclear deterrent for self-defence. This is a great victory of the outstanding Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il and the Workers' Party of Korea's Songun politics and a most striking proof of its validity and might.
 On the tasks facing the whole party and army and all the people to implement the WPK's Songun leadership, the reporter underscored the need to defend and glorify President Kim Il Sung's idea and line on self-reliant defence building and his immortal exploits for it generation after generation and resolutely safeguard Kim Jong Il politically and ideologically and with lives in any adversity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He further said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The People's Army should intensify the movement to win the title of the O Jung Hup-led 7th regiment and thus augment its politico-ideological and military technological might and fully demonstrate its invincible capability as the ranks of human bullets and bombs devotedly defending the leader and a strong revolutionary army that has inherited the spirit of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to establish the trait of attaching importance to the army throughout the society, organize and conduct all work on the principle of giving priority to the military affairs and thus thoroughly implement the Party's military line for self-defence with a view to consolidating the achievements already made in the efforts to place all the people under arms and turn the whole country into a fortress.
 We should give priority to the development of the national defence industry as required by the Songun era so as to convert it into a powerful defence industry in the 21st century capable of providing a sure military technological guarantee for the security of the country and the victorious advance of the revolution and increase the military deterrent of the country in every way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an essential requirement for the successful implementation of the Party's Songun revolutionary line to fully ensure the function and role of the NDC. It is necessary to unconditionally accept and implement to the letter any order and instruction of the NDC and thus more thoroughly establish Kim Jong Il's unitary leadership over the defence work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an important task facing us today to step up the general march for Songun revolution once again and thus augment the overall state power of the country with the military power as the core and bring about a decisive turn in economic construction and in the improvement of the standard of the people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to wage a dynamic patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration in order to decisively foil the machinations of the separatist forces at home and abroad and bring about a fresh epochal phase in the movement for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation is growing tenser and more acute on the Korean Peninsula than ever before due to the U.S. ever-more undisguised hostile policy toward the DPRK and its reckless military provocations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now talking about the six-party talks but in fact, it is zealously inciting hostility toward the DPRK while floating all sorts of sheer fictions, utterly indifferent to the talks. It is only watching for every chance to attack the DPRK while staging large-scale war exercises after listing it as a target of "preemptive attack."
 A preemptive attack is not monopoly of the U.S. and the DPRK will never sit idle till it is exposed to a preemptive attack of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK will closely follow the every move of the U.S. with high revolutionary vigilance. Should the U.S. ignite a war of aggression at any cost, they will mobilize their politico-ideological might and military potentials built up generation after generation under the leadership of the great illustrious Songun commander and mercilessly wipe out the enemies and thus victoriously conclude the stand-off with the U.S.

KCNA Blasts U.S. Human Rights Racket against DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- The United States in its recent 2005-2006 record "Supporting Human Rights and Democracy" malignantly slandered the DPRK again.
 Its contents only increase the aversion to the charade of "human rights and democracy" as it is peppered with U.S. oft-repeated sheer lies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush bellicose group, a group of fascists in the 21st century, is not entitled to talk about human rights and democracy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Is the U.S. not a typical barren land of human rights as it legalizes undisguised wiretapping and constant watch of residents and denies them elementary political rights and vital rights? The U.S., regarding aggression and war, exploitation and pillage as the principal means of its existence prompted by misanthropy, has set up prisons in Iraq, Guantanamo and various other parts of the world and practiced mediaeval torture methods only to stun the world. Is it not the worst human rights abuser in the world?
 It is the U.S. that has earned an ill-fame as a modern-type fascist state.
 Such being a hard fact, the U.S. is talking about "human rights performance" in sovereign states. This only provokes the world people's laughter.
 That is why the international community ridicules the U.S., urging it to mind its P's and Q's whenever it cries out for "human rights". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush administration is pressurizing other countries to accept American-style "liberal democracy" rejected by the people in different parts of the world. This is a vicious challenge to genuine freedom and democracy as it is intended to remodel the world on the American pattern at any cost. This is nothing but a day dream unrealizable in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush fascist group's hysteria of "human rights and democracy" is no more than a vivid expression of contemporary megalomania of the U.S. and its mental and moral frustration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The evermore frantic anti-DPRK smear campaign of the U.S., the enemy of freedom and democracy, only reinforces its people's faith in Korean-style socialism centred on the masses and makes the single-minded unity of its army and people around the supreme headquarters stronger than ever before.
